<h3>{{ _('Bed Visualizer') }}</h3>
<div class="row-fluid">
	<p>In order for this plugin to work properly, you must configure the GCODE commands necessary to send back a Bed Topography Report. Common examples are listed below.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>G29 T</li>
		<li>G81</li>
		<li>M420 V</li>
	</ul>
	<p>If your leveling method requires homing first make sure to enter that as well in the GCODE Commands below.
	<p>If you have Marlin's Auto Temperature Reporting feature enabled you will want to have M155 S30 and M155 S3 surrounding your reporting GCODE command, otherwise the collected data will be tainted with temperature information.</p>
	<p>If you end up requiring multiple commands below it is recommended to enter <span class="label">@BELEVELVISUALIZER</span> just prior to the reporting command. For example:<br>
		<div class="row-fluid">
			G28<br>
			M155 S30<br>
			@BEDLEVELVISUALIZER<br>
			G29 T<br>
			M155 S3<br>
		</div>
	</p>
</div>
<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="control-group">
		<label for="bedlevelvisualizer_command"><i class="icon icon-info-sign" title="GCODE commands to send to printer to retrieve grid data" data-toggle="tooltip"></i> GCODE Commands</label>
		<textarea class="input-block-level" id="bedlevelvisualizer_command" rows="4" data-bind="value: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.bedlevelvisualizer.command"></textarea>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="row-fluid">
	<p>If you run into any problems please check the <a href="https://github.com/jneilliii/OctoPrint-BedLevelVisualizer/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue" target="_blank">Issues</a> for possible fixes or report a bug.</p>
</div>